== Installing Utilmm ==

Note for Debian users: a quick install guide is included at the
bottom of this file

=== Getting the sources

  git clone http://www.laas.fr/~sjoyeux/git/utilmm.git

=== Dependencies and installation instructions
To build the library, you need the following:
 * the boost libraries, including the following:
    boost/thread
    boost/regex
    boost/filesystem
    boost/graph

 * cmake

When all these dependencies are installed, run
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake ..
  make
  make doc

And, as root,
  make install

=== Quick Debian installation guide
Run as root
  apt-get install build-essential libtool libboost-dev libboost-filesystem-dev libboost-thread-dev libboost-regex-dev libboost-graph-dev cmake

Run as a normal user
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake ..
  make
  make doc

Run as root
  make install

